<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1323,1839,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
There is only one specimen in the collections referable to this name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[1129,1322,1839,1865]" pageId="17" pageNumber="34" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1924) Notes on the types of Mycetophilidae (Diptera) described by Staeger and Zetterstedt. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 45, 160 - 168." type="journal article" year="1924">
Edwards (
<number box="[1253,1314,1839,1865]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a good species, larger but close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Staeger, 1840" authorityName="Staeger" authorityYear="1840" box="[854,1319,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Brevicornu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseicolle">
<emphasis box="[854,1120,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Brevicornu griseicolle</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Staeger" box="[1140,1310,1879,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="34" refString="Staeger, R. C. (1840) Systematisk fortegnelse over de i Danmark hidtil fundne Diptera. Tipulariae Fungicolae. Naturhistorisk tidsskrift, 3, 228 - 288." type="journal article" year="1840">
Staeger, 
<number box="[1247,1310,1879,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1840.0">1840</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
After 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[335,525,284,310]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1924) Notes on the types of Mycetophilidae (Diptera) described by Staeger and Zetterstedt. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 45, 160 - 168." type="journal article" year="1924">
Edwards (
<number box="[456,517,284,310]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[535,689,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Brevicornu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis box="[535,689,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">B. canescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been totally overlooked due to a mixing with 
<taxonomicName authority="Zetterstedt, 1852" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Brevicornu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseolum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">B. griseolum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zetterstedt" box="[397,600,324,350]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" refString="Zetterstedt, J. W. (1852) Diptera scandinaviae disposita et descripta. Lundae 11, xii + 4091 - 4545." type="journal article" year="1852">
Zetterstedt, 
<number box="[540,600,324,350]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1852.0">1852</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
[see below]. It is a large distinct species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1896" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Brevicornu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1125,1256,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Brevicornu</emphasis>
<collectingCountry name="Marshall Islands" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Marshall</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[333,392,364,390]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</taxonomicName>
where the Cu­fork is positioned slightly beyond the M­fork. Hence, the species is reinstated with its original name and illustrated here as the first correct record from 
<collectingCountry name="Sweden" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Sweden</collectingCountry>
after the original description.
</paragraph>
